        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] At the beginning of His ministry our Lord did not teach by Parables. “The Sermon on the Mount may be taken as the type of the ‘words of grace’ which He spake ‘not as the Scribes.’ Beatitudes, laws, promises were uttered distinctly, not indeed without similitudes, but with similitudes that explained themselves.” And so He continued for some time. But His direct teaching was met with scorn, unbelief, and hardness. From this time forward “parables” entered largely into His recorded teaching, and were at once attractive and penal. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
